> Earlier today Edison served a copy of the November 20, 2001 letter from
Wes
> Franklin stating that protests to A.L. 1586 are due December 4,
> 2001.  Attached to this e-mail is a copy of the letter TURN sent to the
> Commission's Energy Division  raising some of our concerns regarding
> attempting to implement the CPUC/Edison settlement through the advice
> letter process, and calling upon the Commission to instead address these
> implementation matters in a more appropriate forum.  Today we realized
that
> we should have circulated that letter more widely than we did on Monday.
>
> Please do not hesitate to contact me if you have questions or comments
> about TURN's letter.
>
> Bob Finkelstein
> TURN

A couple of thoughts --

1.	Ashley Brown and Rick have a great relationship.  Don't hesitate to use Rick to find out some details if you need him.

2.	Are we supporting this?  I don't understand why we would agree to make NG the MM with this process / paper?

Thanks.

